Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Bring a large #pot
of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Heat a large dry pan over medium-high heat. Add @bacon{4%ounce}; cook, turning
occasionally and adjusting heat if browning too quickly, until crispy,
~{6-10%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a paper-towel-lined plate. Once
cool enough to handle, roughly chop.

> Bacon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

Carefully discard all but a thin layer of bacon fat from pan.

Once water is boiling, add @rigatoni pasta{6%ounce} to pot. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking
water, then drain.

While pasta cooks, trim and halve @zucchini{1} lengthwise; cut crosswise into
½-inch-thick half-moons. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @onion{1}.

Toss zucchini on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon},
half the @dried oregano{1%teaspoon} (all for 4 servings), @salt{}, and
@pepper{}. Roast on top rack until golden brown and tender, ~{14-16%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pat @chopped chicken breast{10%ounce} dry with paper towels and
season all over with salt and pepper.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Return pan with bacon fat to medium-high heat. Add chicken in a single layer;
cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.
Turn off heat; transfer to a plate. Wipe out pan.

Return pan used for chicken to medium heat. Add a drizzle of oil and onion;
season with @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, a pinch of @chili flakes{1%teaspoon},
salt, and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until onion starts to soften,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @tomato paste{1} and cook, stirring constantly, until slightly darkened,
~{30-60%seconds}.

Add ½ cup reserved pasta cooking water (¾ cup for 4 servings) and
@butter{2%tablespoon} (4 TBSP for 4). Bring to a simmer and cook, stirring
constantly, until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Reduce heat under pan with sauce to low. Stir in drained rigatoni, zucchini,
chicken, and @crème fraîche{4%tablespoon} until everything is evenly coated in
sauce.

> If sauce seems too thick, add splashes of reserved pasta cooking water 1 TBSP
> at a time.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Divide pasta between shallow #bowls{}; top with bacon and
@parmesan cheese{3%tablespoon}. Sprinkle with as many remaining chili flakes as
you like. Serve.